What is e.preventDefault()?
--------------------------------

It stops the default behavior of an event from happening.
 Every HTML element has some default action:

Form → refresh page on submit
Link (<a>) → navigate to another page
Checkbox → toggle checked

preventDefault() cancels that behavior.


let e=document.getElemById('error')

e.foreach((a)=>
{
    a.
})






